          "url": "https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260404033844.1892595-1-joshua.hahnjy@gmail.com/",
          "date": "2026-04-04T03:38:48Z",
          "in_reply_to": null,
          "ack_type": null,
          "is_ongoing": false,
          "submitted_date": null,
          "patch_version": 2,
          "version_history": [
            {
              "version": 2,
              "message_id": "20260404033844.1892595-1-joshua.hahnjy@gmail.com",
              "url": "https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260404033844.1892595-1-joshua.hahnjy@gmail.com/",
              "subject": "[PATCH v2] mm/percpu, memcontrol: Per-memcg-lruvec percpu accounting",
              "date": "2026-04-04T03:38:48Z"
            }
          ],
          "series_items": [],
          "patch_summary": "This patch modifies the Linux kernel's memory accounting system to provide more detailed information about per-memcg-lruvec (per-cgroup, per-node, and per-LRU vector) percpu allocations. It does this by converting a certain type of memory tracking from a per-memcg level to a per-node level, allowing for better visibility into memory pressure on multi-NUMA systems. The patch also introduces separate accounting for node-level statistics and memcg-lruvec statistics, which requires exposing a new function to be used outside of the memory control module. This change improves the kernel's ability to track memory usage at a finer granularity, particularly for percpu allocations, but has a small memory overhead and negligible performance impact.",
          "analysis_source": "llm-per-reviewer",
          "review_comments": [
            {
              "author": "Joshua Hahn (author)",
              "summary": "Author acknowledged a mistake in exporting mod_memcg_lruvec_state, which was unnecessary for this patch and only leftover from another series. The author apologized for the 'noise' and promised no further changes are needed.",
              "sentiment": "POSITIVE",
              "sentiment_signals": [
                "acknowledged_mistake",
                "apologized"
              ],
              "has_inline_review": false,
              "tags_given": [],
              "raw_body": "Hello Matthew, thank you for reviewing my patch!\n\nWhoops, no module uses this symbol in this patch. I was working on a similar\npatch series (accounting zswap statistics on a per-lruvec level [1]) where I did\nthe same thing, and needed to export this so that using it in zsmalloc\nwouldn't break if zram was built as a module.\n\nObviously there's no need for exporting for this patch but I forgot to drop\nthat part when copying this over from that series. Sorry for the noise!\n\nThanks again for catching this. I hope you have a great day!\nJoshua\n\n[1] https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260311195153.4013476-10-joshua.hahnjy@gmail.com/",
              "reply_to": "Matthew Wilcox",
              "message_date": "2026-04-03",
